    "file_upload": "56c39be1-batch_final_prelabeled.json",
    "drafts": [],
    "predictions": [
      407
    ],
    "data": {
      "text": "Nearly half of planned US data centers have been delayed or canceled limited by shortages of power\n\nCompanies like Amazon, Oracle, Meta, Google, and OpenAI have committed over 600B this year to building out datacenters. However, electrical power components like transformers, switchgears, and batteries, are not able to keep up with demand. Exports of these critical parts have increased coming out from China, but it isn't enoughto meet the unsatiable demand for AI in the US. US companies have also increased purchasing from companies from Canada, Mexico, and South Korea, but this is still not enough. Will this change the outlook on other supplier companies like memory and gpus for 2026?"
    },
