    "file_upload": "56c39be1-batch_final_prelabeled.json",
    "drafts": [],
    "predictions": [
      547
    ],
    "data": {
      "text": "Lyft will go to top floor\n\nBeen looking at $LYFT and honestly can’t figure out why it’s this cheap. Market cap is around $5B, they did $6.3B in revenue last year, and pulled in over $1B in free cash flow. P/E is like 2 (yeah there’s a tax thing inflating it, forward is closer to 9, still cheap). About 16% of the float is short, institutions own basically all of it, so the actual float floating around is pretty thin.\n\nThe thing that got me interested is the FREENOW acquisition they closed last summer. They paid €175M to BMW/Mercedes for it and now they’re in 11 countries — basically doubled their addressable market overnight. Plus there’s the whole AI angle where agents will need real-world labor marketplaces to actually do stuff in the physical world, and Lyft already has the drivers and the infrastructure. Could be wrong, but at this price the downside seems pretty limited. Just buying shares, not getting fancy with options.​​​​​​​​​​​​​​​​"
    },
